h3. PROBLEM:

When inserting label on the database, JIRA is currently using Literals, meaning each statement is in clear text, including values. 

 
{code:java}
2016-10-10 21:05:40,723 http-nio-8718-exec-8 admin 1265x96x1 1p9brgo /secure/AjaxIssueAction.jspa 1ms "INSERT INTO public.label (ID, FIELDID, ISSUE, LABEL) VALUES ('10000', 'null', '10601', 'test')"
{code}
h3. SUGGESTION:

Is there by any chance that JIRA will be using BIND variables in the future where the same insert is executed with different values sent to the variables
{code}
insert into LABEL (ID,FIELDID,ISSUE,LABEL) values (:id,:fieldid,:issue,:label) 
{code}
 

I believe this will improve in terms of performance.

